videos.headline: Miami defense breaks out Turnover Chain on Wisconsin's first drive
videos.description: Wisconsin's Jonathan Taylor tries to finish off a tough run and the Miami defense knocks the ball loose as Dee Delaney recovers.

videos.headline: Taylor really sells delay for Wisconsin first down
videos.description: Wisconsin's Jonathan Taylor is standing still when Alex Hornibrook gives him the ball, but he turns on the jets for a 19-yard run to set up a Wisconsin field goal.

videos.headline: Homer rumbles into end zone for Miami TD
videos.description: Travis Homer takes the carry 5 yards up the middle for the score to cap the 7-play drive as Miami leads 7-3.

videos.headline: Dallas bounces outside for long Miami TD run
videos.description: Miami's DeeJay Dallas takes the direct snap and beats two Wisconsin defenders to the edge to score from 39 yards out as Miami extends their lead to 14-3.

videos.headline: Wisconsin intercepts Miami screen pass
videos.description: Andrew Van Ginkel does his best Wisconsin-alum J.J. Watt impression and intercepts the screen pass at the line of scrimmage to give the Badgers possession in scoring position.

videos.headline: Wisconsin capitalizes with TD pass
videos.description: Wisconsin turns a turnover into a touchdown after Alex Hornibrook throws a 20-yard pass to Danny Davis III who just breaks the pylon as the Badgers cut the deficit to 14-10.

videos.headline: Taylor sets single-season freshman rushing mark
videos.description: On this run, Jonathan Taylor sets the record for most rushing yards in a season by a freshman, passing Adrian Peterson's Oklahoma mark.

videos.headline: Ramesh hurdles for Wisconsin first down
videos.description: Austin Ramesh catches the pass in the flat and leaps over the Miami defender for the first down.

videos.headline: Taylor hauls in Wisconsin TD with one hand
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook throws it up for A.J. Taylor who secures the catch with one hand in the end zone as Wisconsin has scored 14 unanswered points.

videos.headline: Hornibrook keeps drive alive
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook steps up in the pocket and delivers a 21-yard pass to Kendric Pryce to the Miami 10-yard line with under a minute left in the half.

videos.headline: Richt gets personal foul for touching offical
videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt loses his cool and costs his team a penalty in the red zone.

videos.headline: Hornibrook-Davis connection extends Wisconsin lead before half
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook finds Danny Davis III in the end zone for the duo's second score as Wisconsin takes a 24-14 lead at half.

videos.headline: Richt on penalty with official: 'If you watch the tape you'll see'
videos.description: Mark Richt explains his outburst where he grabbed an official and cost his team a penalty as Miami trails 24-14 at half.

videos.headline: Wisconsin pouring it on for first-half lead
videos.description: The Badgers score 21 unanswered points and go into the half up 24-14 on Miami.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Wisconsin pouring it on for first-half lead) 2017/12/30 SOTFULL

videos.headline: Rosier draws defense in and lobs Miami TD
videos.description: Miami's Malik Rosier looks like he's going to take off running, but lobs a long pass to Lawrence Cager who slips behind the Wisconsin defense for the touchdown.

videos.headline: Wisconsin intercepts Miami in end zone
videos.description: Miami is threatening to score when Derrick Tindal intercepts Malik Rosier in the end zone to give the Badgers the ball back.

videos.headline: Cager's clutch catch sets up Miami FG
videos.description: On third down, Malik Rosier connects with Lawrence Cager to move Miami into scoring position, and the ensuing field goal cuts the Hurricanes' deficit to 27-24.

videos.headline: Davis catches 3rd TD for Wisconsin
videos.description: Alex Hornibrook finds Danny Davis III in the end zone for Davis' third touchdown catch of the night as the Badgers extend their fourth-quarter lead to 34-24.

videos.headline: Thomas provides spark for Miami
videos.description: As time winds in the fourth, Malik Rosier launches a pass to Jeff Thomas who comes down with the 48-yard reception.

videos.headline: INT seals Orange Bowl win for Badgers
videos.description: Ryan Connelly comes down with the interception as Wisconsin tops Miami 34-24 in the Capital One Orange Bowl.

videos.headline: Hornibrook shines for Badgers with 4 TD passes
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook credits the Badgers' preparation for his success against the vaunted Hurricanes defense.

videos.headline: Chryst: Badgers 'made the most' of their moment
videos.description: Wisconsin head coach Paul Chryst discusses leading the Badgers to victory in the Capital One Orange Bowl and setting a school-record 13 wins in a season.

videos.headline: Wisconsin stops Miami in Orange Bowl showdown
videos.description: Alex Hornibrook throws four touchdowns, three to Danny Davis III, on 258 yards as the Badgers take down the Hurricanes 34-24 to win the Capital One Orange Bowl.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Wisconsin stops Miami in Orange Bowl showdown) 2017/12/30 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: Hornibrook turns in career performance to beat Miami defense
videos.description: Brian Griese and Steve Levy react to Alex Hornibrook's 4-touchdown performance in a game where Wisconsin had 74 more offensive snaps than Miami.

videos.headline: Hornibrook's four scores lead Wisconsin past Miami
videos.description: Alex Hornibrook throws for 258 yards and four touchdowns in the Badgers' 34-24 win against the Hurricanes in the Capital One Orange Bowl.
